add status not equal 'queued' to the match stage

Looking at the provided code, you need to add a condition to the `matchStage` object to filter out ACH requests with status 'queued'. Here's the modified code:

```js
// Excerpt from: const calculateAchTimeRangeStats
const matchStage = {
  createdAt: {},
  status: { $ne: 'queued' }
}
```

This adds a MongoDB query condition using the `$ne` (not equal) operator to exclude records where the status field is 'queued'.
I want it to use the Enums.AchRequestStatus.QUEUED

I understand you want to use the enum constant instead of the string literal. Here's the corrected version:

```js
// Excerpt from: const calculateAchTimeRangeStats
const matchStage = {
  createdAt: {},
  status: { $ne: Enums.AchRequestStatus.QUEUED }
}
```

This uses the enum constant `Enums.AchRequestStatus.QUEUED` instead of the string literal 'queued', which is a better practice as it maintains consistency and prevents typos.
