show if the account.deleted is true or false, if it is true, then show account.deletedAt
The code has an extra `<td>` without content and is missing a closing `</td>` for the third column. I'll fix that issue and add the requested display of deletion status. Here's the corrected code:

```js
// Excerpt from: 
<tbody>
    {bankAccounts.map((account, index) => (
        <tr key={index}>
            <td>{account.metaBankName}</td>
            <td>{account.metaAccountName}</td>
            <td>{account.metaAccountMask}</td>
            <td>{account.status}</td>
            <td>
                {account.deleted ? (
                    <>Deleted: {new Date(account.deletedAt).toLocaleString()}</>
                ) : (
                    'Not Deleted'
                )}
            </td>
        </tr>
    ))}
</tbody>
```

This adds a new column that shows:
- "Not Deleted" if account.deleted is false
- "Deleted: [formatted timestamp]" if account.deleted is true, displaying the deletedAt date in a readable format
